pokedex: Extremely cautious, they take shifts to maintain a constant watch of their nest. They feel insecure without a lookout.

name: Watchog
pokedex: They make the patterns on their bodies shine in order to threaten predators. Keen eyesight lets them see in the dark.

name: Lillipup
pokedex: The long hair around its face provides an amazing radar that lets it sense subtle changes in its surroundings.

name: Herdier
pokedex: It loyally follows its Trainer's orders. It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

name: Stoutland
pokedex: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Intelligent, good-natured, and valiant, it's a trustworthy partner on rescue teams.

name: Purrloin
pokedex: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.

name: Liepard
pokedex: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

name: Pansage
pokedex: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to induce stress.

name: Simisage
pokedex: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: Pansear
pokedex: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600º F.

name: Simisear
pokedex: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

name: Panpour
pokedex: It does not thrive in dry environments. It keeps itself damp by shooting water stored in its head tuft from its tail.

name: Simipour
pokedex: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful it can destroy a concrete wall.

name: Munna
pokedex: Always floating in the air, Munna eat the dreams of people and Pokémon. They expel different gases depending on the types of dreams they eat.

name: Musharna
pokedex: Munna fall into a permanent trance when they evolve. Musharna can manipulate gases, often shaping them into things from dreams it has eaten.

name: Pidove
pokedex: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

name: Tranquill
pokedex: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.

name: Unfezant
pokedex: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

name: Blitzle
pokedex: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

name: Zebstrika
pokedex: These ill-tempered Pokémon have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: Roggenrola
pokedex: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

name: Boldore
pokedex: Because its energy was too great to be contained, the energy leaked and formed orange crystals.

name: Gigalith
pokedex: The solar energy absorbed by its body's orange crystals is magnified internally and fired from its mouth.

name: Woobat
pokedex: Suction from its nostrils enables it to stick to cave walls during sleep. It leaves a heart-shaped mark behind.

name: Swoobat
pokedex: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

name: Drilbur
pokedex: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.

name: Excadrill
pokedex: Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph more than 300 feet below the surface.

name: Audino
pokedex: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radar-like ability to understand its surrounding through slight sounds.

name: Timburr
pokedex: These Pokémon appear at building sites and help out with construction. They always carry squared logs.

name: Gurdurr
pokedex: They strengthen their bodies by carrying steel beams. They show off their big muscles to their friends.

name: Conkeldurr
pokedex: They use concrete pillars as walking canes. They know moves that enable them to swing the pillars freely in battle.

name: Tympole
pokedex: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

name: Palpitoad
pokedex: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.

name: Seismitoad
pokedex: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.

name: Throh
pokedex: When they encounter foes bigger than themselves, they try to throw them. They always travel in packs of five.

name: Sawk
pokedex: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

name: Sewaddle
pokedex: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

name: Swadloon
pokedex: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

name: Leavanny
pokedex: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

name: Venipede
pokedex: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggresive.

name: Whirlipede
pokedex: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

name: Scolipede
pokedex: Highly aggressive, it chases down its foes with quick movements. It attacks relentlessly with its horns and toxic neck spikes until it prevails.

name: Cottonee
pokedex: They go wherever the wind takes them. On rainy days, their bodies are heavier, so they take shelter beneath big trees.

name: Whimsicott
pokedex: They appear riding whirlwinds. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.

name: Petilil
pokedex: By pruning the leaves on its head with regularity, this Pokémon can be grown into a fine plump shape!

name: Lilligant
pokedex: It's well liked by other Pokémon because of its beauty. The flower on its head needs constant care, or it will soon wither and rot.

name: Basculin
pokedex: Savage, violent Pokémon, Basculin are always fighting each other over territory. Anglers love the fight this Pokémon puts up on the hook.

name: Sandile
pokedex: It moves along below the sand's surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.

name: Krokorok
pokedex: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings, even in darkness.

name: Krookodile
pokedex: It can expand the focus of its eyes, enabling it to see objects in the far distance as if it were using binoculars.

name: Darumaka
pokedex: Darumaka's droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.

name: Darmanitan
pokedex: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.

name: Maractus
pokedex: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

name: Dwebble
pokedex: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

name: Crustle
pokedex: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.

name: Scraggy
pokedex: It immediately headbutts anyone that makes eye contact with it. Its skull is massively thick.

name: Scrafty
pokedex: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.

name: Sigilyph
pokedex: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.

name: Yamask
pokedex: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.

name: Cofagrigus
pokedex: They pretend to be elaborate coffins to teach lessons to grave robbers. Their bodies are seemingly covered in pure gold.

name: Tirtouga
pokedex: Based on studies of its skeletal structure, it can apparently dive to and survive at ocean depths of over half a mile.

name: Carracosta
pokedex: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A wave generated by one of them is enough to capsize a tanker.

name: Archen
pokedex: These Pokemon glided down from treetops to snag prey, but were notorious for giving up easily. Perhaps this is why they went extinct...

name: Archeops
pokedex: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey, but give up easily. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

name: Trubbish
pokedex: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokémon.

name: Garbodor
pokedex: They absorb garbage and make it part of their bodies. They shoot a poisonous liquid from their right-hand fingertips.

name: Zorua
pokedex: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

name: Zoroark
pokedex: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

name: Minccino
pokedex: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

name: Cinccino
pokedex: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. They are playful and caring, but can adroitly wield their scarves and icy tendrils!

name: Gothita
pokedex: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

name: Gothorita
pokedex: It's said that when stars shine in the night sky, this Pokémon will spirit away sleeping children. Some call it the Witch of Punishment.

name: Gothitelle
pokedex: A criminal who was shown his fate by a Gothitelle went missing that same day and was never seen again. They can see life spans.

name: Solosis
pokedex: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they can survive in any environment.

name: Duosion
pokedex: When their brains, now divided in two, are thinking the same thoughts, these Pokémon exhibit their maximum power.

name: Reuniclus
pokedex: These remarkably intelligent Pokémon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.

name: Ducklett
pokedex: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

name: Swanna
pokedex: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.

name: Vanillite
pokedex: Theoretically, this Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. Their breath is -58° F.

name: Vanillish
pokedex: They cool down the surrounding air and create ice particles, which they use to freeze their foes.

name: Vanilluxe
pokedex: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokémon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.

name: Deerling
pokedex: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

name: Sawsbuck
pokedex: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

name: Emolga
pokedex: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane. They have to be careful not to get struck by lightning!

name: Karrablast
pokedex: When they feel threatened, they spit an acidic liquid to drive attackers away. This Pokémon targets Shelmet.

name: Escavalier
pokedex: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

name: Foongus
pokedex: For some reason, this Pokémon resembles a Poké Ball. They release poison spores to repel those who try to catch them.

name: Amoonguss
pokedex: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.

name: Frillish
pokedex: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.

name: Jellicent
pokedex: Their favorite food is life energy. The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent's habitat: all sunken, all vanished, all lost.

name: Alomomola
pokedex: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

name: Joltik
pokedex: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. They soak up electricity because they can't produce a charge on their own.

name: Galvantula
pokedex: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.

name: Ferroseed
pokedex: They stick their spikes into cave walls and absorb the minerals they find in the rock.

name: Ferrothorn
pokedex: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

name: Klink
pokedex: Interlocking two bodies and spinning around generates the energy they need to live.

name: Klang
pokedex: Spinning minigears are rotated at high speed and repeatedly fired away. It is dangerous if the gears don't return.

name: Klinklang
pokedex: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

name: Tynamo
pokedex: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.

name: Eelektrik
pokedex: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

name: Eelektross
pokedex: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.

name: Elgyem
pokedex: It controls tremendous psychic power. Most reports of alien sightings are actually just people mistaking Elgyem for an alien.

name: Beheeyem
pokedex: Sometimes found drifting above wheat fields, this Pokémon can control the memories of its opponents.

name: Litwick
pokedex: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.

name: Lampent
pokedex: It arrives near the moment of death and steals the spirit from the body.

name: Chandelure
pokedex: Being consumed in Chandelure's flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.

name: Axew
pokedex: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

name: Fraxure
pokedex: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.

name: Haxorus
pokedex: Haxorus attack other powerful Pokemon for sport or territory. Their axe-blade tusks are their pride and joy... and are incredibly destructive.

name: Cubchoo
pokedex: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.

name: Beartic
pokedex: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. It swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

name: Cryogonal
pokedex: They are composed of chains of ice crystals. They capture prey with these chains of ice, absorbing them into itself.

name: Shelmet
pokedex: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

name: Accelgor
pokedex: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.

name: Stunfisk
pokedex: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of energy.

name: Mienfoo
pokedex: They have mastered elegant combos. As they concentrate, their battle moves become swifter and more precise.

name: Mienshao
pokedex: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

name: Druddigon
pokedex: Despite dwelling in caves, it warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.

name: Golett
pokedex: These Pokémon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.

name: Golurk
pokedex: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.

name: Pawniard
pokedex: They fight at Bisharp's command. They cling to their prey and inflict damage by sinking their blades into it.

name: Bisharp
pokedex: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.

name: Bouffalant
pokedex: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. They headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.

name: Rufflet
pokedex: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.

name: Braviary
pokedex: The more scars they have, the more respect these brave soldiers of the sky receive from their peers.

name: Vullaby
pokedex: They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They only attack the weakest Pokémon.

name: Mandibuzz
pokedex: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.

name: Heatmor
pokedex: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant's steel bodies and consume their insides.

name: Durant
pokedex: Durant dig nests in mountains. They build their complicated, interconnected tunnels in mazes.

name: Deino
pokedex: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

name: Zweilous
pokedex: Since their two heads do not get along and compete with each other for food, they always eat too much.

name: Hydreigon
pokedex: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.

name: Larvesta
pokedex: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

name: Volcarona
pokedex: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.

name: Cobalion
pokedex: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.

name: Terrakion
pokedex: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.

name: Virizion
pokedex: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.

name: Tornadus
pokedex: Tornadus expels massive squalls from its tail as it flies about. Its power is great enough to sweep entire towns away.

name: Thundurus
pokedex: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies across regions discharging bolts at whim.

name: Reshiram
pokedex: According to myth, if people ignore truth and become corrupt, Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.

name: Zekrom
pokedex: Mythology tells us that if people lose the righteousness in their hearts, their kingdoms will be razed by Zekrom's lightning.

name: Landorus
pokedex: The energy that comes pouring from its tail increases the nutrition in the soil, making crops grow to great size.

name: Kyurem
pokedex: This legendary Pokémon of ultracold air waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.

name: Keldeo
pokedex: They say that Keldeo must survive harsh battles and fully develop the horn on its forehead before this Pokémon's true power will awaken.

name: Meloetta
pokedex: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

name: Genesect
pokedex: This bug Pokémon was mutated by genetic experimentation and augmented with powerful technology. It is considered the ultimate weapon.

name: Chespin
pokedex: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

name: Quilladin
pokedex: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.

name: Chesnaught
pokedex: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

name: Fennekin
pokedex: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

name: Braixen
pokedex: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

name: Delphox
pokedex: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

name: Froakie
pokedex: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

name: Frogadier
pokedex: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: Greninja
pokedex: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

name: Bunnelby
pokedex: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

name: Diggersby
pokedex: More powerful than an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it's finished digging, it lounges lazily.

name: Fletchling
pokedex: These friendly Pokemon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

name: Fletchinder
pokedex: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.

name: Talonflame
pokedex: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

name: Scatterbug
pokedex: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

name: Spewpa
pokedex: The beaks of bird Pokémon are often irratated by its bristly body. It spews powder to defend itself.

name: Vivillon
pokedex: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

name: Litleo
pokedex: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.

name: Pyroar
pokedex: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride’s cubs.

name: Flabebe
pokedex: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.

name: Floette
pokedex: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the power of flowers to battle.

name: Florges
pokedex: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

name: Skiddo
pokedex: Thought to be one of the first Pokemon to be domesticated by humans, it has an energized, playful disposition.

name: Gogoat
pokedex: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a thunderous battle of clashing horns.

name: Pancham
pokedex: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

name: Pangoro
pokedex: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.

name: Furfrou
pokedex: Historically, these Pokemon were the designated guardians of the king of the Telius region.

name: Espurr
pokedex: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.

name: Meowstic
pokedex: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It's when they're protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.

name: Honedge
pokedex: Apparently this Pokemon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

name: Doublade
pokedex: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.

name: Aegislash
pokedex: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

name: Spritzee
pokedex: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

name: Aromatisse
pokedex: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.

name: Swirlix
pokedex: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and as sticky as cotton candy.

name: Slurpuff
pokedex: Its sense of smell is a million times better than a human's, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It's like it can see with its nose!

name: Inkay
pokedex: It draws prey near with its blinking lights and then wraps them up in its long tentacles and holds them in place.

name: Malamar
pokedex: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.

name: Binacle
pokedex: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.

name: Barbaracle
pokedex: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.

name: Skrelp
pokedex: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on any prey that approaches unawares.

name: Dragalge
pokedex: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge dwell, never to return.

name: Clauncher
pokedex: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

name: Clawitzer
pokedex: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

name: Helioptile
pokedex: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

name: Heliolisk
pokedex: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.

name: Tyrunt
pokedex: This Pokémon is selfish and likes to be pampered. It can also inflict grievous wounds on its Trainer just by playing around.

name: Tyrantrum
pokedex: The king of the ancient world, it can easily crunch a car with the devastating strength of its enormous jaws.

name: Amaura
pokedex: It lived in cold areas in ancient times. It's said that when Amaura whinnies, auroras appear in the night sky.

name: Aurorus
pokedex: Its diamond-shaped crystals expel freezing air. It's said that when this Pokémon cries, auroras appear in the night sky.

name: Sylveon
pokedex: Sylveon cuts an elegant figure as it dances lightly around, feelers fluttering, its soothing aura calming fights.

name: Hawlucha
pokedex: It drives opponents to exhaustion with agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with its signature pose and awesome over-the-top-rope maneuver!

name: Dedenne
pokedex: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.

name: Carbink
pokedex: It has slept underground for thousands of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.

name: Goomy
pokedex: It's covered in a slimy membrane that makes any punches or kicks slide off it harmlessly. It lives in damp, shady places.

name: Sliggoo
pokedex: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can't see well.

name: Goodra
pokedex: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokemon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.

name: Klefki
pokedex: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.

name: Phantump
pokedex: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.

name: Trevenant
pokedex: It can control trees at will. A deadly curse falls upon anyone cutting down trees in forests where Trevenant dwell.

name: Pumpkaboo
pokedex: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

name: Gourgeist
pokedex: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.

name: Bergmite
pokedex: It blocks opponents' attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.

name: Avalugg
pokedex: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.

name: Noibat
pokedex: They live in pitch black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

name: Noivern
pokedex: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.

name: Xerneas
pokedex: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

name: Yveltal
pokedex: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

name: Zygarde-50%
pokedex: This is Zygarde's form when about half of its pieces have been assembled. It plays the role of monitoring the ecosystem.

name: Diancie
pokedex: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: Hoopa
pokedex: It gathers things it likes and pushes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

name: Volcanion
pokedex: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

name: Rowlet
pokedex: Flies noiselessly on delicate wings. Rowlets are also known to endearingly use Trainers' pockets or bags as nests.

name: Dartrix
pokedex: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

name: Decidueye
pokedex: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision that they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.

name: Litten
pokedex: It doesn't allow its emotions to be easily seen. Earning its trust takes time. It prefers solitude.

name: Torracat
pokedex: It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.

name: Incineroar
pokedex: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. It uses any tactics available to win and excels at brutal, no-holds-barred battles.

name: Popplio
pokedex: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It is famous for being a hard worker.

name: Brionne
pokedex: It cares deeply for its companions. When its Trainer is feeling down, it performs a cheery dance to try and help.

name: Primarina
pokedex: Its singing voice is its chief weapon in battle. This Pokémon's Trainer must prioritize the daily maintenance of its throat at all costs.

name: Pikipek
pokedex: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and for nesting.

name: Trumbeak
pokedex: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

name: Toucannon
pokedex: Within its beak, its internal gas ignites, explosively launching seeds with enough power to pulverize boulders.

name: Yungoos
pokedex: It wanders around in a never-ending search for food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustion and falls asleep on the spot.

name: Gumshoos
pokedex: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location, but it is always snoozing by nightfall.

name: Grubbin
pokedex: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees and slurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.

name: Charjabug
pokedex: Its body is capable of storing electricity. People are grateful to have one around on camping trips!

name: Vikavolt
pokedex: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.

name: Crabrawler
pokedex: It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What little meat they contain is rich and delicious.

name: Crabominable
pokedex: It just throws punches indiscriminately. In times of desperation, it can lop off its own pincers and fire them like rockets.

name: Oricorio
pokedex: It captivates its opponents with its dazzling dance moves. When they let their guard down, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

name: Cutiefly
pokedex: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it's able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.

name: Ribombee
pokedex: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.

name: Rockruff
pokedex: This Pokémon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer's side.

name: Lycanroc
pokedex: When properly raised from a young age, it will become a trustworthy partner that will absolutely never betray its Trainer.

name: Wishiwashi
pokedex: Wishiwashi assemble in this formation to face off against strong foes. It boasts a strength that earned it the name "demon of the sea."

name: Mareanie
pokedex: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

name: Toxapex
pokedex: Those attacked by Toxapex's poison will suffer intense pain for three days and three nights. Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.

name: Mudbray
pokedex: It has a stubborn, individualistic disposition. Eating dirt, making mud, and playing in the mire all form part of its daily routine.

name: Mudsdale
pokedex: Its strength, stamina, and stubbornness are unprecedented. It easily hauls 10 ton loads and splinters concrete foundations.

name: Dewpider
pokedex: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.

name: Araquanid
pokedex: Despite what its appearance suggests, it cares for others. If it finds weak, vulnerable Pokémon, it protects them and brings them into its water bubble.

name: Fomantis
pokedex: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.

name: Lurantis
pokedex: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis' vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.

name: Morelull
pokedex: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

name: Shiinotic
pokedex: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.

name: Salandit
pokedex: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.

name: Salazzle
pokedex: Filled with pheromones, its poisonous gas can be diluted for use in the production of luscious perfumes.

name: Stufful
pokedex: A touch from anyone except a known friend sends it into a surging frenzy. It is an incredibly dangerous Pokémon.

name: Bewear
pokedex: This Pokémon has the habit of hugging its companions. Many Trainers have left this world after their spines were squashed by its hug.

name: Bounsweet
pokedex: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.

name: Steenee
pokedex: This Pokémon is always bouncing around energetically. Other Pokémon are attracted by its lively appearance and pleasant aroma.

name: Tsareena
pokedex: Its long, striking legs aren't just for show, but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

name: Comfey
pokedex: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won't wither once they're attached to a Comfey.

name: Oranguru
pokedex: This Pokémon abides deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.

name: Passimian
pokedex: Passimian live in groups of about 20, with each member performing an assigned role. They battle with hard berries for weapons.

name: Wimpod
pokedex: This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.

name: Golisopod
pokedex: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater, or even air, right in two.

name: Sandygast
pokedex: It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of its sand-mound body.

name: Palossand
pokedex: Buried beneath the castle are masses of dried-up bones from those whose vitality it has drained.

name: Pyukumuku
pokedex: These Pokémon line the beaches. The sticky mucus that covers their bodies can be used to soothe sunburned skin. How convenient!

name: Type: Null
pokedex: Due to the danger that this synthetic Pokémon may go on a rampage, it wears a control mask to restrain its power.

name: Type: Full
pokedex: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.

name: Minior
pokedex: This Pokémon was born from mutated nanoparticles and cannot remain exposed for long. Its shell is part of its core body but takes on different properties.

name: Komala
pokedex: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.

name: Turtonator
pokedex: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.

name: Togedemaru
pokedex: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.

name: Mimikyu
pokedex: There was a scientist who peeked under Mimikyu's old rag in the name of research. The scientist died of a mysterious disease.

name: G-Stunfisk
pokedex: It uses conspicuous powers to lure prey in as it lies in wait. Stunfisk keeps its jagged steel fins clamped down using telepathy.

name: Drampa
pokedex: This Pokémon is friendly to people and loves children most of all. It comes from deep in the mountains to play with children it likes in town.

name: Dhelmise
pokedex: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually part of its body.

name: Jangmo-o
pokedex: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.

name: Hakamo-o
pokedex: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.

name: Kommo-o
pokedex: When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.

name: Tapu Koko
pokedex: It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper but forgets what made it angry an instant later.

name: Tapu Lele
pokedex: As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore good health on the spot.

name: Tapu Bulu
pokedex: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it leeches energy from the creatures it attracts.

name: Tapu Fini
pokedex: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.

name: Cosmog
pokedex: In ages past, it was called the child of the stars. It is said to be a Pokémon from another world, but no specific details are known.

name: Cosmoem
pokedex: The shell that encases it is harder than any known material. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of the stars.

name: Solgaleo
pokedex: This Pokémon is said to be a male evolution of Cosmog. At the activation of its third eye, it departs for another world.

name: Lunala
pokedex: It is said to be a female evolution of Cosmog. When its third eye activates, away it flies to another world.

name: Nihilego
pokedex: Producing a strong neurotoxin, those infested by it suddenly become violent. Sometimes it can be observed behaving like a young girl.

name: Buzzwole
pokedex: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.

name: Pheromosa
pokedex: One of the Ultra Beasts. It only touches things to get rid of them, perhaps because it senses some uncleanness in this world.

name: Xurkitree
pokedex: One of the mysterious life-forms known as Ultra Beasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanate from its entire body, according to witnesses.

name: Celesteela
pokedex: One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it burn down a forest by expelling gas from its two arms.

name: Kartana
pokedex: One of the Ultra Beast life-forms, it was observed cutting down a gigantic steel tower with one stroke of its blade.

name: Guzzlord
pokedex: Gobbling mountains and swallowing whole buildings, it appears to be eating constantly. Yet its droppings have never been found.

name: Necrozma
pokedex: Light is the source of its energy. If it is not devouring light, impurities build up in it and on it, and Necrozma darkens and stops moving.

name: Magearna
pokedex: Its mechanized body is merely a vessel. Its true self is its Soul-Heart, an artificial soul.

name: Marshadow
pokedex: It causes people to despair wherever it goes. Saddened by this, it usually hides in the shadows and never appears.

name: Poipole
pokedex: An Ultra Beast that lives in a different world, it cackles wildly as it sprays its opponents with poison from the needles on its head.

name: Naganadel
pokedex: One kind of Ultra Beast, it fires a glowing, venomous liquid from its needles. This liquid is also immensely adhesive.

name: Stakataka
pokedex: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

name: Blacephalon
pokedex: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It is apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

name: Zeraora
pokedex: It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.

name: Rattata
pokedex: Night after night, they sneak into people's homes seeking food. A massive outbreak of them has become an issue of public concern.

name: Raticate
pokedex: It has an incredibly greedy personality. Its nest is filled with more food gathered by the Rattata at its direction than it could possibly eat.

name: A-Raichu
pokedex: It focuses psychic energy into its tail to lift it. It then rides it like it's surfing!

name: A-Sandshrew
pokedex: Its ice-covered body lets it slide across the ground with bullet-like speed, sending its enemies flying when it hits them.

name: A-Sandslash
pokedex: It runs across snow-covered plains at high speeds. It developed thick, sharp claws to plow through the snow.

name: A-Vulpix
pokedex: They live together in a skulk, helping one another. Before eating their prey, they freeze it solid with their –58 degree Fahrenheit breath.

name: A-Ninetales
pokedex: Some said that deities visited mountains where Ninetales live, so in times long past, no one was allowed to go into those mountains.

name: A-Diglett
pokedex: Its head sports an altered form of whiskers made of metal. When in communication with its comrades, its whiskers wobble to and fro.

name: A-Dugtrio
pokedex: Its shining gold hair provides it with protection. It’s reputed that keeping any of its fallen hairs will bring bad luck.

name: Hippopolush
pokedex: Hippopolush loves to splash around, but somehow still thrives in hot, arid deserts. It is viewed as instrumental in many desert ecosystems.

name: Hippoasis
pokedex: Hippoasis produces plant life and water, allowing many desert species to survive that would otherwise be unable to.

name: A-Geodude
pokedex: Its body is a magnetic stone. Iron sand attaches firmly to the portions of its body that are particularly magnetic.

name: A-Graveler
pokedex: They eat rocks and often get into a scrap over them. The shock of Graveler smashing together causes a flash of light and a booming noise.

name: A-Golem
pokedex: It fires rocks charged with electricity. Even if the rock isn't fired that accurately, just grazing an opponent will cause numbness and fainting.

name: Tarountula
pokedex: The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of Scyther, this Pokémon's natural enemy.

name: Spidops
pokedex: It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before they even notice.

name: A-Exeggutor
pokedex: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers while within it awakened a sleeping dragon.

name: A-Marowak
pokedex: When it beats opponents with its bone, the cursed flames spread to them. No amount of water will stop those flames from burning.

name: Zygarde-10%
pokedex: Born when around 10% of Zygarde's cells have been gathered from all over, this form is skilled in close-range combat.

name: Lycanroc
pokedex: The more intimidating the opponent it faces, the more this Pokémon's blood boils. When it attacks, does so without reservation.

name: Lycanroc
pokedex: Bathed in the setting sun of dusk, Lycanroc has undergone a special kind of evolution. An intense fighting spirit underlies its cold expression.

name: Santadelie
pokedex: Once a year, it gives gifts to children from a magical sleigh pulled by flying Stantler.

name: Chemera
pokedex: It is in agony when inside a Pokeball. Researchers speculate that this is a result of Chemera being composed primarily of corrupted Pokeball data.

name: Alkaboros
pokedex: Being so acclimated to pain makes Alkaboros a horrifyingly difficult opponent. That, and its fiery, oozing, nightmarish body, of course.

name: Muskoat
pokedex: They live in herds in the tundra. When threatened, they spin up a poisonous chemical that can be spit out or even secreted. This turns its fur purple.

name: Musktox
pokedex: Large herbivores that live in the tundra. They have long lived in harmony with humans, but their poisonous secretions make them difficult to domesticate.

name: Boreaptor
pokedex: These former jungle hunters, after surviving an ice age, have now acclimated themselves exclusively to colder regions.

name: Velocicle
pokedex: It has an entire arsenal of weapons that make it a lethal predator, from its spined whip-like tail to its icy fangs and venomous claws.

name: Claycotta
pokedex: Long ago, a great Emperor created an army of Claycotta to wage war against all of the known world.

name: Claymord
pokedex: Natural leaders, these Pokemon were once commanders in an army that waged war against all of the known world.

name: Korvia
pokedex: They care deeply for their friends. Inexperienced as knights, Korvia can be a bit overzealous in charging into battle or overprotecting their trainer.

name: Impugil
pokedex: A Pokemon once renowned for kindness, diabolical experiments to remove its Fairy typing have distorted it into a fiend.

name: Diabollyon
pokedex: The most deplorable and wicked of Pokemon, horrific experiments have contorted it into an irredeemably twisted monster.

name: Valkyrok
pokedex: These warrior spirits are said to have saved the Telius region from foreign invaders in a great war long ago.

name: Flaminquent
pokedex: It has a brash and difficult attitude, convinced it always knows best. It is known to form troublemaking gangs with Pokemon like Scraggy.

name: Scimenco
pokedex: It is cocky and vicious. It dances around to draw attention to itself, but meet its gaze and it may suddenly and violently attack you!

name: Mindigo
pokedex: The body is just a vessel for the mask. It's said that the mask houses three evil spirits constantly fighting for control of the vessel.

name: Wendraugr
pokedex: The spirit of a mindless necrophage that wrestles for control of the bodies of Mindigo. The vessel it possesses becomes a disgusting, insatiable monster.

name: Wendrifr
pokedex: The spirit of a demented wizard that wrestles for control of the bodies of Mindigo. The vessel it possesses becomes a disfigured, manic necromancer.

name: Wendreavr
pokedex: The spirit of an elemental essence that wrestles for control of the bodies of Mindigo. The vessel it possesses becomes a malicious, serpentine djinn.

name: Bamboozle
pokedex: An utterly bizarre and unpredictable trickster, this Pokemon totters around aimlessly. If it invites you to play a game, you should politely decline.

name: Parastrain
pokedex: The fungi has become a wretched hivemind, part of the same life form as the bug body. The grim visage of its spores and pincers shake even the bravest souls.

name: Aristeroth
pokedex: A phantom created when there is a failed heroic effort. It seeks to regain its lost memories through contact with opponents' struggles.

name: Meltan
pokedex: Failed attempts at resurrecting the legendary Pokemon Melmetal eventually resulted in the creation of this species.

name: Melmetal
pokedex: It was used over 3000 years ago to create metals. Modern technology revived it, but with a liquefied, toxic body.

name: Moaidea
pokedex: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Moaidea's face contained a mysterious power.

name: Graffitiki
pokedex: Ancient people of the Alola Region despised Graffitiki for bringing sun that would destroy their crops. This is apparently no longer a problem, however.

name: Harprey
pokedex: An intelligent apex predator, humans fear its piercing shrieks. It traps prey, using its barbed leg talons to envenom and haul off young Bouffalant.

name: Alphanonymus
pokedex: Unown resonance with modified Odd Keystones created this composite being. Further testing is required on this strange new variant.

name: Regaledy
pokedex: It holds pure moonlight in its crown. With an iron fist, it rules over and preserves all clean forests.

name: Terachnitas
pokedex: Its heart seeks chaos and upheaval. Mustering other foul, creeping things, it brings to ruin all that is ordered.

name: Colosswhal
pokedex: One of the rarest non-legendary Pokemon, some explore vast oceans seeking the mystical power their horns supposedly hold.

name: Divapason
pokedex: A true ice queen, this dramatic Pokemon strikes both fear and awe with its sad, melodic cries and powerful wintry blasts.

name: Aetherhine
pokedex: Living miles underground, this Pokémon is one of the rarest to find in the wild. Researchers claim it is somehow integral to the planet's health.

name: Caracoldron
pokedex: Caracoldron can live for hundreds of years despite struggling to store energy. Instead, they erupt or hail meteors down for metabolic regulation.

name: Cascora
pokedex: Cascora are instrumental to the health of the seas. Scientists have tried to augment them for use in water treatment facilities.

name: Distortree
pokedex: Chemical manipulations have allowed this Pokemon to exhibit plant-like traits including pebble-like seeds and bark as hard as stone.

name: Cloisine
pokedex: Augmented by strange DNA, it works tirelessly in food industries. Strangely, it has developed a rapacious appetite for Fairy-type Pokemon.

name: Cherraphim
pokedex: It can manipulate solar energy. Passionate in everything it does, it most loves joyful celebrations and scourging evildoers.

name: Carillona
pokedex: Its bells resonate with various energy waves. Mostly uncontrollable, its tendency to disrupt telecommunication networks gives it a mischievous reputation.

name: Tentakraken
pokedex: Eldritch stories of the deep; pulsing red lights from the abyss... Its dreadful tentacles and energy blasts are the horror of all waters.

name: Veisstacean
pokedex: Very little is known about it. Researchers who dare venture deep within the icy crevasses where it dwells are never seen again.

name: Seraphair
pokedex: Historical records indicate that because Seraphair can read the intents of others, it arbitrated entire societies with its verdicts.

name: Vesupius
pokedex: Their cocoons are made of magma. They absorb nutrients from the earth and sun until they have enough energy for evolution.

name: Citrusaur
pokedex: It flies by flapping its broad leaves. The bunch of fruit that grows around its neck is deliciously sweet. In the spring, it scatters pollen from its neck.

name: Canoplethio
pokedex: The process of creating Canoplethio was completely revolutionary, hardening Tropius's immune and skeletal systems with DNA splicing.

name: Scarlacia
pokedex: Mystical properties attributed to Flygon are actually the work of this Pokemon, which disappears into sandstorms until its body returns to sand itself.

name: Bisheerie
pokedex: It appears their spirits were preserved in fossils instead of their eel-like bodies. But with enough dead tissue, they can materialize.

name: Solstwins
pokedex: Solstwins was once worshipped by Amokkins as the avatar of the dual-gods Gronia and Swamki. It's widely recognized as a religious symbol.

name: Nihilight
pokedex: This Pokemon maintains the cycles of human grief through denial, bargaining, and acceptance. It is highly intelligent and talks to humans through electromagnetic pulses.

name: Druidem
pokedex: This Pokemon maintains the cycles of nature through light, soil, and nutrients. It is highly intelligent and talks to nature through ley lines.

name: Immortelius
pokedex: Their cocoons are made of magma. They absorb nutrients from the earth and sun until they have enough energy for evolution.

name: H. Avalugg
pokedex: This Pokémon barrels along steep mountain paths, cleaving through the deep snow. Sometimes other Pokemon hitch a ride on its back!

name: Tapu Rava
pokedex: Redacted.

name: Mosqewer
pokedex: Its long needle mouth can pierce bones and suck out their marrow. The abdominal blood sac is far less vulnerable than it looks.

name: Scarecroach
pokedex: This terrifying Pokemon is actually possessed by a hivemind of bugs which control the movements and actions of the scarecrow body.

name: Cramorant
pokedex: It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight.

name: Motocyclops
pokedex: Famous songs have been written of fools who ghost ride this whip: they are driven straight down the highway to hell!

name: Orchestrum
pokedex: It's said that the power of a long-lost song stirred this Pokemon to life. It always keeps perfect time.

name: Mr. Rime
pokedex: Its amusing routine makes it very popular. But when in battle, its performance usually means its opponents are the ones that break a leg!

name: Swashlocker
pokedex: Yo-ho, yo-ho, a Pokemon holding a gun! Yo-ho, yo-ho; why is the rum always gone?

name: Sphincubus
pokedex: Capable of speech, scientists believe these puzzling statues were used as hosts by a seemingly sentient primordial virus.

name: Meowstic
pokedex: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck to dust.

name: Zamazenta
pokedex: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

name: Shockra
pokedex: Its mysterious origins are tied to Amokkin legends, but some rumors claim it was created by PokeStar Studios in the Unova Region.

name: Forgiant
pokedex: These leviathans of the deep form their own Pokemon societies through their unmatched creative and organizational power.

name: Platytuudz
pokedex: Its impressive bulk belies its incredibly quirky and humorous personality. Multitudes of trainers are drawn to it because of its joyful idiosyncrasies.

name: Sepulchrest
pokedex: Featured in ancient Amokkin heraldry, this bird-like spirit prophesies the death of the sun and the end of the world.

name: Anubrakhan
pokedex: Its appearance is dignified. This 'taskmaster of the sands' will dominate the weak and ambush the strong.

name: Frospire
pokedex: Synthesized by humans, its partly organic composition can be used to both provide shelter in and directly aid in the study of harsh climates.

name: Morpeko
pokedex: Hormones completely warp its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.

name: Basculegion
pokedex: Basculegion spawns from the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream.

name: Faultopia
pokedex: REDACTED

name: Alltross
pokedex: Believing its own experiential and revelatory knowledge to be supreme, it is locked in eternal bloodshed with Nephilamia and Parallaxon.

name: Nephilamia
pokedex: Believing its own disciplined and creative traditions to be supreme, it is locked in eternal bloodshed with Alltross and Parallaxon.

name: Parallaxon
pokedex: Believing its perpetually updating technological faculties to be supreme, it is locked in eternal bloodshed with Alltross and Nephilamia.

name: G-Darumaka
pokedex: The colder they get, the more energetic they are. They freeze their breath to make snowballs, using them as ammo for playful snowball fights.

name: G-Darmanitan
pokedex: Though it has a gentle disposition, it's also very strong. It will quickly freeze the snowball on its head before going for a headbutt.

name: Purrzurker
pokedex: Purrzurker would form tribes to raid and plunder human towns together. Now, however, they seem only interested in attacking other Pokemon.

name: Deerling
pokedex: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

name: Sawsbuck
pokedex: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

pokedex: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

name: Deerling

name: Sawsbuck
pokedex: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

name: Grookey
pokedex: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

name: Thwackey
pokedex: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

name: Rillaboom
pokedex: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

name: Scorbunny
pokedex: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon's body. Once that happens, it's ready to fight at full power.

name: Raboot
pokedex: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.

name: Cinderace
pokedex: Lightning quick, it maneuvers a ball with its feet. Its strikes are hard and precise and leave arcs of sparks in their wake.

name: Sobble
pokedex: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won't be able to resist weeping.

name: Drizzile
pokedex: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

name: Inteleon
pokedex: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

name: Skwovet
pokedex: It eats berries nonstop—a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It'll crawl into people's homes, searching for yet more berries.

name: Greedent
pokedex: This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.

name: Rookidee
pokedex: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.

name: Corvisquire
pokedex: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.

name: Corviknight
pokedex: This Pokémon regins supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.

name: Blipbug
pokedex: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn't.

name: Dottler
pokedex: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

name: Orbeetle
pokedex: It emits impressive psychic energy from its gigantic brain center to observe and study everything around it, up to six miles away.

name: Nickit
pokedex: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off of its ill-gotten gains.

name: Thievul
pokedex: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

name: Gossifleur
pokedex: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.

name: Edelgoss
pokedex: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

name: Wooloo
pokedex: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

name: Dubwool
pokedex: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You'll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

name: Chewtle
pokedex: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

name: Drednaw
pokedex: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

name: Yamper
pokedex: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.

name: Boltund
pokedex: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltound can run nonstop for three full days.

name: Rolycoly
pokedex: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

name: Carkol
pokedex: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

name: Coalossus
pokedex: It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Applin
pokedex: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it's just an apple and nothing more.

name: Flapple
pokedex: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. It flies on wings of apple skin and can also change its shape into that of an apple.

name: Appletun
pokedex: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in Pokémon it preys on.

name: Silicobra
pokedex: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.

name: Sandaconda
pokedex: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

name: Eternatus
pokedex: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.

name: G-Ponyta
pokedex: This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.

name: G-Rapidash
pokedex: Brave and prideful, this Pokémon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.

name: Grunjam
pokedex: It manipulates its chemical makeup to produce electricity. The voltage may be low, but the protrusions on its head work like speakers!

name: Charismuse
pokedex: When this Pokémon sounds as if it's strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.

name: Sizzlipede
pokedex: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

name: Centiskorch
pokedex: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

name: Clobbopus
pokedex: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

name: Grapploct
pokedex: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

name: Sinistea
pokedex: The teacup in which this Pokémon makes its home is a famous piece of antique tableware. Many forgeries are in circulation.

name: Polteageist
pokedex: Trainers Polteageist trusts will be allowed to experience its distinctive flavor and aroma firsthand by sampling just a tiny bit of its tea.

name: Snymph
pokedex: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. If you don't have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

name: Snowhim
pokedex: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.

name: Sylphlake
pokedex: If you're too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokémon is also known as the Silent Witch.

name: Impidimp
pokedex: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.

name: Morgrem
pokedex: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, its trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.

name: Grimmsnarl
pokedex: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.

name: Obstagoon
pokedex: Notorious for seedy underworld dealings, it relies mostly on its wits and intimidation. Disreputable trainers use it as an enforcer.

name: Cursola
pokedex: After its environment was polluted, this once vibrant and vivacious Pokémon is now a ghostly shell of its former self.

name: Curscora
pokedex: Be cautious of its toxic, ectoplasmic body. Its pollutants are said to blight everything around it.

name: Sirfetch'd
pokedex: Only Farfetch'd that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon's leek withers, it will retire from combat.

name: Ingast
pokedex: It's said that this Pokémon was formed when a vengeful spirit was drawn to an ancient clay tablet.

name: Deildolon
pokedex: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you'll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.

name: Milcery
pokedex: This Pokémon sweetens foul-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

name: Alcremie
pokedex: Make sure to treat this Pokemon well! When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it’s decorated with cream.

name: Phalinks
pokedex: Five of these tenacious warriors are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.

name: Pincurchin
pokedex: It stores electricity in each spine. Even if one gets broken off, it still continues to emit electricity for at least three hours.

name: Snom
pokedex: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.

name: Frosmoth
pokedex: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. The temperature of its wings is less than −290 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Stonjourner
pokedex: Once a year at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle. It is rumored they create rifts between worlds.

name: Bloodritch
pokedex: REDACTED

name: Kubfu
pokedex: Protected by its family unit, Kubfu's uncultivated Wushu energy is an irresistable food source for predatory Ultra Beasts.

name: Urshifu
pokedex: Inhabiting the mountains of a strange land, this Pokémon hones its alien Wushu powers to slay the beasts and monsters that threaten its livelihood.

name: Cufant
pokedex: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It's also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

name: Copperajah
pokedex: Copperajah's trunk has incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder. Their green skin is resistant to water.

name: Duraludon
pokedex: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's lightweight, strong, and considerably agile. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

name: Dreepy
pokedex: After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.

name: Drakloak
pokedex: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

name: Dragapult
pokedex: When it isn't battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.

name: Zacian
pokedex: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

name: Lycanroc
pokedex: Bathed in the breaking light of dawn, Lycanroc has undergone a special kind of evolution. An ascetic poise underlies its cheery demeanor.

name: Alcremie
pokedex: Make sure to treat this Pokemon well! When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.

name: Alcremie
